article.headline: Wagner 72, Brown 59
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Jamal Smith scored 20 of his 25 points in the first half and Wagner held off a late rally to defeat Brown 72-59 on Wednesday night. Smith, a freshman guard, connected on nine of 13 shots from the field including all four of his three-point shots. Durell Vinson scored 12 of his 14 points in the second half for Wagner (3-1). Wagner outscored Brown 18-0 early in the first half for a 22-3 lead. Smith scored seven points during this run and the Seahawks held Brown (1-4) without a basket for a stretch of 9:42. Sam Manhanga led Brown with 14 points. The Seahawks led 52-28 early in the second half when Brown made a run led by P.J. Flaherty (11 points) and Damon Huffman, who was 4-for-4 at the free throw line and scored on a driving layup as Brown pulled within 59-52 with 3:40 to play. Wagner converted seven of its last eight free throw attempts late in the game. Wagner's Mark Porter was 6-for-6 at the line and extended his streak of consecutive free throws made to 19.
